g 1410456 - remove get latency implementation because makes use of dlopen. r=padenot\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1Mc2dSk0hlc", "files": ["media/libcubeb/src/cubeb_opensl.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1123e0934d4da3da078f63dc822c29d5e826c117", "parents": ["ff486aaaddbbca9895a8a15d8a3995c4be6a26fb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Chronopoulos \u003cachronop@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1410456 - remove preferred sample rate implementation because makes use of dlopen. r=padenot\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: jBZ3oewbjh", "files": ["media/libcubeb/src/cubeb_opensl.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bc670bbf9e2c0d75a8d7a66b6c66e6764bef4e58", "parents": ["1123e0934d4da3da078f63dc822c29d5e826c117"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Chronopoulos \u003cachronop@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1410456 - get mixer latency from JNI instead of system library. r=jchen,padenot,snorp\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3YciuVu25JO", "files": ["media/libcubeb/src/cubeb-jni-instances.h", "media/libcubeb/src/cubeb-jni.cpp", "media/libcubeb/src/cubeb-jni.h", "media/libcubeb/src/cubeb_opensl.c", "media/libcubeb/src/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dcd12fd91dd0b2554cde0e0acbcc50eeb671bc38", "parents": ["bc670bbf9e2c0d75a8d7a66b6c66e6764bef4e58"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Chronopoulos \u003cachronop@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1410456 - Keep the old mechanism for the older versions that jni method is not available. r=padenot\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3jXf3wuXqZu", "files": ["media/libcubeb/src/android/cubeb-output-latency.h", "media/libcubeb/src/android/cubeb_media_library.h", "media/libcubeb/src/cubeb_opensl.c"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "96def2ab5e5efb61cbd0672e2e0bfbd7b9458c88", "parents": ["dcd12fd91dd0b2554cde0e0acbcc50eeb671bc38"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Chronopoulos \u003cachronop@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1410456 - Add new files in update.sh script. r=padenot\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5Nmdd8WOlJc", "files": ["media/libcubeb/update.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "11ca9fbd181f4902d8e03de6c92c545733f69db8", "parents": ["96def2ab5e5efb61cbd0672e2e0bfbd7b9458c88"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Chronopoulos \u003cachronop@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1410456 - Pass in cubeb JNIEnv instead of JavaVM. r=padenot\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Cf8FvZzShVv", "files": ["media/libcubeb/src/cubeb-jni-instances.h", "media/libcubeb/src/cubeb-jni.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "343e35827f30aa23a8ef38e175b68a7a5e79308c", "parents": ["11ca9fbd181f4902d8e03de6c92c545733f69db8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Alex Chronopoulos \u003cachronop@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1410456 - Update cubeb from upstream to eb3409e.r=achronop\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Ie9hhw1Prlw", "files": ["media/libcubeb/README_MOZILLA"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "22c153aa809b6daa02728795044b3506f4f1aba5", "parents": ["343e35827f30aa23a8ef38e175b68a7a5e79308c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1428795 - Move recommended prefs to component. r=automatedtester\n\nSetting the recommended preferences is not a task specific to the\nTCP listener.  It makes more sense to set these in the Marionette\nXPCOM component where we manage the Marionette lifetime.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: G2RuLhKnX9X", "files": ["testing/marionette/components/marionette.js", "testing/marionette/server.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "65fa19a430ba699ea4a0b01fb33eb02e59ef8fd8", "parents": ["22c153aa809b6daa02728795044b3506f4f1aba5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1428795 - Set MOZ_MARIONETTE in component. r=automatedtester\n\nSetting the MOZ_MARIONETTE environment variable is not a task that\nnaturally belongs to the TCP listener.  This patch moves it to the\nMarionette XPCOM component.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 7896Sv91wFy", "files": ["testing/marionette/components/marionette.js", "testing/marionette/server.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6f92c0b0abe832829cafc4342a773f2cafeed242", "parents": ["65fa19a430ba699ea4a0b01fb33eb02e59ef8fd8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1428795 - Uninitalise Marionette on xpcom-will-shutdown. r=automatedtester\n\nMarionette was previously uninitialised when xpcom-shutdown fired.\nThis may be too late to reset preferences and other state related\nto the browser.\n\nThis patch moves Marionette to run uninitialisation code on\nxpcom-will-shutdown.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3ytX2k2rrOp", "files": ["testing/marionette/components/marionette.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d1cb6c61dcf8dee823bf9416cd7046af8c1dd00b", "parents": ["6f92c0b0abe832829cafc4342a773f2cafeed242"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1428795 - Reset Marionette state when initialisation fails. r=automatedtester\n\nIf Marionette throws inside try...catch block that spawns the TCP\nlistener, we fail to reset the altered recommended preferences to\ntheir original state, leaving a possibility of tainting the profile.\nBy calling the uninitialisation code when an error is thrown we\nensure all relevant state gets reset.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: XiiIEFMZQY", "files": ["testing/marionette/components/marionette.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "672e7d5d8f40a04ccd87b0f84eb4ade0f19cbdd4", "parents": ["d1cb6c61dcf8dee823bf9416cd7046af8c1dd00b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1441226 - Rename NoAlertOpenError to NoSuchAlertError. r=whimboo\n\nTo match the WebDriver specification error code names, this patch\nrenames the NoAlertOpenError type to NoSuchAlertError.\n\nIts string error code (the status property) is still correct.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DhWz1tn6DsT", "files": ["testing/marionette/driver.js", "testing/marionette/error.js", "testing/marionette/test_error.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fbe5a80f2f5b2a7235fd17ba296c66b38846efeb", "parents": ["672e7d5d8f40a04ccd87b0f84eb4ade0f19cbdd4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1426082 - Remove superfluous transport tests. r=whimboo\n\nThis drops the tests for Marionette protocol level 2.  Protocol levels\nbelow 2 were removed some time ago:\n\n\thttps://bugzilla.mozilla.org/show_bug.cgi?id=1409030\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GsrdeldnoNH", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/test_transport.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f57a1cd84e0c347e26d11e683f790df8387ddbdb", "parents": ["fbe5a80f2f5b2a7235fd17ba296c66b38846efeb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1426082 - Enable test_transport.py. r=whimboo\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LIhRX6uoJFh", "files": ["testing/marionette/harness/marionette_harness/tests/unit/unit-tests.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bc82a797a301aa5b543eba804d6b9af2df8515b2", "parents": ["f57a1cd84e0c347e26d11e683f790df8387ddbdb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1439657 Remove Time Precision Reduction from Console Timestamps r=baku\n\nWe currently reduce the precision of timestamps emitted by console.time\nin the main context, but not in a Worker. Because web page content cannot\nread the content of messages emitted to the console (right?), we don't\nactually need to reduce the precision of this data.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EfpIEICy0tX", "files": ["dom/console/Console.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "828515186ebc425c586fccef80abadb147bac245", "parents": ["bc82a797a301aa5b543eba804d6b9af2df8515b2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437564 - Stop setting a text color for checked toolbarbuttons on Windows since the native background is mostly transparent and the color should be inherited. r=johannh\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Hgp8DhBrkGU", "files": ["toolkit/themes/windows/global/toolbarbutton.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5736dea94b68cf137fc64b8ea2b3b31fdb204ea9", "parents": ["828515186ebc425c586fccef80abadb147bac245"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Anthony Ramine \u003cn.oxyde@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #20145 - Kill RUSTC_HAS_PR45225 \ud83c\udf89 (from servo:rm-rustc-hack); r=emilio\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 30f33eba9665f5ffdc0648515db7cede68778202", "files": ["servo/components/style/build.rs", "servo/components/style/properties/build.py", "servo/components/style/properties/longhand/inherited_svg.mako.rs", "servo/components/style/properties/longhand/pointing.mako.rs", "servo/geckolib-rust-toolchain"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4dd745a165437b1763878b30bb9bb9e58958fcb5", "parents": ["5736dea94b68cf137fc64b8ea2b3b31fdb204ea9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kevin Brosnan \u003ckbrosnan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Kevin Brosnan - Bug 1441579 - Install ncurses-compat-libs for Fedora as part of mach bootstrap r=nalexander\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6TsufMMzjIc", "files": ["python/mozboot/mozboot/centosfedora.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "603a1b645a9cbdfb58895a54ced4cd3348a65344", "parents": ["4dd745a165437b1763878b30bb9bb9e58958fcb5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Csoregi Natalia \u003cncsoregi@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset fbe5a80f2f5b (bug 1441226) for linting Doc failures. CLOSED TREE", "fi