h enforces the distrust of Syamntec roots from\nBug 1409257. It is ultimately destined for Firefox 60.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8Vpxdflk9Wu", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/security-prefs.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "97eade2b82c7ad778bd4dbc247163a587f3465b0", "parents": ["0e06932d93c20f596e29e2b0b30fde9e79b663cb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Glenn Watson \u003cgithub@intuitionlibrary.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #20166 - Update WR (async scene building fix) (from glennw:update-wr-async); r=jdm\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 320c7f409dafb1629c8c5d47ba16f6d84c0770cc", "files": ["servo/Cargo.lock"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a6d21e9e202722006bbb20e6f5bbb22b70e6a5ca", "parents": ["97eade2b82c7ad778bd4dbc247163a587f3465b0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrew McCreight \u003ccontinuation@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1442403 - Stop building xpcom/typelib/xpt/ with MOZ_NO_MOZALLOC. r=glandium\n\nThis was added in bug 1081000 to support linking XPT tests, but those\ntests were removed in bug 1248534, part 1, so this shouldn't be needed\nany more.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: I1V2XVBaMG7", "files": ["xpcom/typelib/xpt/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b5f5774139ed5a921ccc31dc3fddff36ce18d8e0", "parents": ["a6d21e9e202722006bbb20e6f5bbb22b70e6a5ca"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brian Grinstead \u003cbgrinstead@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1442507 - Remove unused sborient attribute in scrollbar binding; r=enndeakin+6102\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5nsunzHMJVu", "files": ["toolkit/content/widgets/scrollbar.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c5c7ad8944453536cdfd9bd5387c5acd87fe3909", "parents": ["b5f5774139ed5a921ccc31dc3fddff36ce18d8e0"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Josh Matthews \u003cjosh@joshmatthews.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #20168 - Improve disk usage of doc builds (from servo:jdm-patch-16); r=emilio\n\nContinuing the war on disk space usage, I noticed the doc builder on servo-linux4 was growing over time without bound.\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 1475b54f5d9ce456070d91ef65f468ecf57f4f6e", "files": ["servo/etc/ci/upload_docs.sh"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "aa6b6dd214e967122606f53b444bbcb55d14ef4d", "parents": ["c5c7ad8944453536cdfd9bd5387c5acd87fe3909"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreea Pavel \u003capavel@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to autoland a=merge on a CLOSED TREE", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "affbbe1c5829beb2f6448a32a253e46224102adb", "parents": ["aa6b6dd214e967122606f53b444bbcb55d14ef4d", "9552b5f236a56a89edbe0625231502b3d8fe5bcd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thom Chiovoloni \u003ctchiovoloni@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1441666 - Add helper functions for inserting encrypted records to the test server r=kitcambridge\n\nThis also converts some of our tests to use them. In particular,\n\n1. All of the new functions should have coverage.\n2. None of the existing tests should assume we can decrypt records by\n   JSON.parsing them.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: y7Hw3q9Wko", "files": ["services/sync/tests/unit/head_http_server.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_bookmark_duping.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_bookmark_engine.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_bookmark_smart_bookmarks.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_clients_engine.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_history_engine.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_password_engine.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_syncengine_sync.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7bc4e7d466a3b7fd258b89b1fcf9f41ebf9ff8f2", "parents": ["affbbe1c5829beb2f6448a32a253e46224102adb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thom Chiovoloni \u003ctchiovoloni@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1408551 - Set hasDupe on outgoing bookmarks when using the buffer r=kitcambridge\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BU5Hbkn5OKH", "files": ["services/sync/modules/engines/bookmarks.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_bookmark_engine.js", "toolkit/components/places/SyncedBookmarksMirror.jsm", "toolkit/components/places/tests/sync/test_bookmark_deletion.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/sync/test_bookmark_kinds.js", "toolkit/components/places/tests/sync/test_bookmark_value_changes.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cca108d5a695dd00aa0e527c6764ec041f7d69e1", "parents": ["7bc4e7d466a3b7fd258b89b1fcf9f41ebf9ff8f2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Thom Chiovoloni \u003ctchiovoloni@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425152 - Update lastSync timestamp even if some sync engines failed r=markh\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: HTWuZsp5Evb", "files": ["services/sync/modules/stages/enginesync.js", "services/sync/tests/unit/test_errorhandler_2.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "640e1784f2dbd5a71f08cc32195183bdfdad6f42", "parents": ["cca108d5a695dd00aa0e527c6764ec041f7d69e1"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ken VanDine \u003cken.vandine@canonical.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1442419 - Fix failure to open files after downloading with snap r=jlorenzo\n\nThis fix does several things:\n * Removes the mime cache generated by the desktop-gtk3 remote part\n * Installs a stub shared-mime-info database\n * Set default association for all types to use xdg-open\n\nNote: There is still work[1] to be completed in snapd, adding OpenFile\nsupport to xdg-open.  Landing this is harmless though, it will fail\nsilently just as it does today but will start working when the snapd\nfeature lands.\n\n1. https://github.com/snapcore/snapd/pull/4766\nopening requested files,\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1eeOLeVN8xQ", "files": ["taskcluster/docker/firefox-snap/mime-handler.xml", "taskcluster/docker/firefox-snap/mimeapps.list", "taskcluster/docker/firefox-snap/snapcraft.yaml.in"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3800cbeee1e3d01cb5c7688fb8f50bca72ad7442", "parents": ["640e1784f2dbd5a71f08cc32195183bdfdad6f42"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1441916 - Add hooks in APZCTreeManager to respond to layer tree changes. r=botond\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4dDYQ1YGOO", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa85e73273106b6a2919e4ff7b7c0d0ba33c79c7", "parents": ["3800cbeee1e3d01cb5c7688fb8f50bca72ad7442"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1441916 - Replace the code to clear focus targets with the simpler hook. r=botond\n\nInstead of keeping track of all the layers ids that we've seen during\nthe tree walk, we can now just get notified when a layer subtree is\nremoved, and clear out the state for that layers id at that point.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DVlWX3upWJ6", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/FocusState.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/FocusState.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1ecd27281e6bd0c84a97e0aa518fbd0e634a86bb", "parents": ["fa85e73273106b6a2919e4ff7b7c0d0ba33c79c7"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1441916 - Move APZTestData from the LayerTreeState structure into the APZ. r=botond\n\nThis encapsulates the APZTestData better inside APZCTreeManager, which\nwe will want once we allow the hit-test tree update to happen on a\nthread other than the compositor thread.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 66uSsagVfEu", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/CrossProcessCompositorBridgeParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5b0855476e63525730ba4374b3445b55f1eda38f", "parents": ["1ecd27281e6bd0c84a97e0aa518fbd0e634a86bb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1441916 - Remove calls to GetIndirectShadowTree inside APZCTreeManager. r=botond\n\nCalling GetIndirectShadowTree and holding on to the result - or holding\non to pointers from the LayerTreeState - is fine on the compositor\nthread, but if we want to allow APZ to accept layer updates and scroll\noffset sampling on some other thread, then we should avoid doing this.\nThis patch replaces calls to GetIndirectShadowTree with the\nCallWithIndirectShadowTree function and ensures anything that outlives\nthe function is held on to with a RefPtr. Of course, this only takes\ncare of the more superficial concerns - we will also need to robustify\nthose classes' implementations to handle being called from multiple\nthreads; that will be tackled later.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: E40JGFjooPo", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "243444effec32210c60750978e980c39d80d8648", "parents": ["5b0855476e63525730ba4374b3445b55f1eda38f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1441916 - Introduce the notion of the APZ sampler thread. r=botond\n\nThe sampler thread is similar to the controller thread in that it doesn't\ncorrespond to a particular actual thread, but instead introduces an\nabstraction that allows us to reason about code flow and data ownership\nthat is logically grouped on a single thread. For now the sampler thread\nremains mapped to the compositor thread, but eventually we will allow\nit to be render backend thread when webrender is enabled.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: D6i2t5lDvkv", "files": ["gfx/layers/Compositor.cpp", "gfx/layers/Compositor.h", "gfx/layers/apz/public/IAPZCTreeManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/public/IAPZCTreeManager.h", "gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.h", "gfx/layers/apz/src/AsyncPanZoomController.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/AsyncPanZoomController.h", "gfx/layers/apz/src/HitTestingTreeNode.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/OverscrollHandoffState.h", "gfx/layers/apz/util/APZThreadUtils.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/util/APZThreadUtils.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "928e83cc61780c24d52a048a4c1cf023f12f1b46", "parents": ["243444effec32210c60750978e980c39d80d8648"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1441916 - Modify the static GetAPZCTreeManager to return an IAPZCTreeManager. r=botond\n\nThis static function has only two call sites. One (in GPUProcessManager)\nis unused, so it can be removed. The other (in\nInProcessCompositorSession) takes the returned APZCTreeManager and\nexposes it as an IAPZCTreeManager. Instead of doing this, we can simply\nexpose it as an IAPZCTreeManager from CompositorBridgeParent itself, to\nreduce the number of places that can potentially grab a handle to the\nAPZCTreeManager.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BjLf6GSsnKz", "files": ["gfx/ipc/GPUProcessManager.cpp", "gfx/ipc/GPUProcessManager.h", "gfx/ipc/InProcessCompositorSession.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorThread.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5bbb3e69e745abf1b9b2962a9134dbb07de105cb", "parents": ["928e83cc61780c24d52a048a4c1cf023f12f1b46"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1441916 - Introduce an APZSampler interface for APZCTreeManager. r=botond\n\nThis interface should be used for accessing any sampler-thread functions\non APZCTreeManager. Eventually the interface will handle thread\ndelegation so that if it is called from a thread that is not the sampler\nthread it will redirect the calls appropriately. For now it just allows\nto logically group the public APZCTreeManager methods that are to be run\non the sampler thread.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GArPvjfuYYr", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/public/APZSampler.h", "gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.cpp", "gfx/layers/apz/src/APZCTreeManager.h", "gfx/layers/apz/src/APZSampler.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.h", "gfx/layers/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "da64726bf399abe8936889dc2e2c04acc8cec782", "parents": ["5bbb3e69e745abf1b9b2962a9134dbb07de105cb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mark Banner \u003cstandard8@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1442597 - Can't drag/copy the Mobile bookmarks folder shortcut. r=mak\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: OqKDMEqxeA", "files": ["browser/components/places/tests/browser/browser_copy_query_without_tree.js", "toolkit/components/places/Bookmarks.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a170c4ecc80df942507efeb9bd6ecacbec0126d1", "parents": ["da64726bf399abe8936889dc2e2c04acc8cec782"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Nico Grunbaum", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1441260 - unify API for setting extmaps in AudioConduit r=dminor,mjf\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8PmvQyk32WW", "files": ["media/webrtc/signaling/src/media-conduit/AudioConduit.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/media-conduit/AudioConduit.h", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/media-conduit/MediaConduitInterface.h", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/media-conduit/VideoConduit.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/media-conduit/VideoConduit.h", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/TransceiverImpl.cpp", "media/webrtc/signaling/src/peerconnection/TransceiverImpl.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fa1869480dd5b6b9d29303d1cdb657f07c0e2b7e", "parents": ["a170c4ecc80df942507efeb9bd6ecacbec0126d1"], 