when drawing justify-content areas; r=gl\n\nSo far, we are drawing the entire line area, and then cutting out the various\nmargin boxes from each item, in order to show where justify-content applies.\nThis is dangerous because that means clearing pixels in a canvas where we're\ndrawing tons of other stuff, and it's easy to accidentally clear unwanted\nthings.\nInstead, now we just draw the justify-content where needed only.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LJN6Fl1by4l", "files": ["devtools/server/actors/highlighters/flexbox.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "91b5d3f7409fff1c6b091dc0e8906fa6a76ae7fc", "parents": ["75ccc12de3267a8876946fc96f22189b7ef5ba32"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andrea Marchesini \u003camarchesini@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444150 Performance.measure(name) should not throw if name is one of the readonly attribute of the Performance interface, r=valentin", "files": ["dom/performance/Performance.cpp", "dom/performance/tests/test_performance_user_timing.js", "testing/web-platform/tests/user-timing/invoke_with_timing_attributes.html", "testing/web-platform/tests/user-timing/measure_exceptions_navigation_timing.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2e0412dd3fc90ac56d86f2c1846f004d3477e22b", "parents": ["91b5d3f7409fff1c6b091dc0e8906fa6a76ae7fc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Robert Longson \u003clongsonr@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1325320 - change SVGGeometryElement::GetOrBuildPath to take DrawTarget as a pointer since all its callers have drawTarget as a pointer themselves.\nThis is consistent with most other methods that take a drawTarget parameter r=dholbert", "files": ["dom/svg/SVGGeometryElement.cpp", "dom/svg/SVGGeometryElement.h", "layout/svg/SVGGeometryFrame.cpp", "layout/svg/nsSVGClipPathFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2bd1e128872221c9d8ffedf5c04ddbd0f7ded051", "parents": ["2e0412dd3fc90ac56d86f2c1846f004d3477e22b"], "tags": []}, {"a