"default", "desc": "Bug 1444614 - Avoid initializing gBrowser and gBrowser.tabContainer early in the urlbar binding constructor. r=Gijs\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Lfv4d8RzhmZ", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/base/content/urlbarBindings.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6379a27eb701e6e455c039d222e58019360af344", "parents": ["c97c9a7a66da925f0193df9175674f383eb1db28"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cosmin Sabou \u003ccsabou@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge autoland to mozilla-central. a=merge", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "7b8e91ebc597e1c68009cb94a2c3891cde591ac4", "parents": ["310045d2fdae1edc54c1891cd4b70cfb868285d8", "6379a27eb701e6e455c039d222e58019360af344"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Cosmin Sabou \u003ccsabou@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge inbound to mozilla-central. a=merge", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "e0eacfc97568bc270e61839c60ae787fb76c4f07", "parents": ["7b8e91ebc597e1c68009cb94a2c3891cde591ac4", "0bc390d8397f210bf67d5ef89b8b07c5ba4d1107"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444082 - sync reader mode to github tip ( 8525c6af36d3badbe27c4672a6f2dd99ddb4097f ), r=johannh\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LZLFf9kyUR5", "files": ["mobile/android/tests/browser/robocop/reader_mode_pages/not_an_article.html", "toolkit/components/reader/JSDOMParser.js", "toolkit/components/reader/Readability.js", "toolkit/components/reader/ReaderWorker.js", "toolkit/components/reader/test/readerModeNonArticle.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "733da5dbad32b2de372687527367596f1f7aa4a2", "parents": ["6379a27eb701e6e455c039d222e58019360af344"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brindusan Cristian \u003ccbrindusan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to autoland. a=merge CLOSED TREE", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "3b7db5bf4dfbf6aeeb8195ccb65aa5bf6e56009d", "parents": ["733da5dbad32b2de372687527367596f1f7aa4a2", "e0eacfc97568bc270e61839c60ae787fb76c4f07"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444625 - Set gBrowser properties directly on the object rather than sequentially in init(). r=Gijs\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3fBLokkFMnP", "files": ["browser/base/content/tabbrowser.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "511cd50ae276e761e97b78f14465343b69277764", "parents": ["3b7db5bf4dfbf6aeeb8195ccb65aa5bf6e56009d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437295 - Promise-ify some of the paint/flushing methods. r=botond\n\nThis is functionally a no-op but it makes code cleaner, particularly\nsome of the changes in a future patch.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5UoT3aNJaPz", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/apz_test_utils.js", "testing/mochitest/tests/SimpleTest/paint_listener.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e2d541a790ea4419dc366ac9dc5d76a7ece662fc", "parents": ["511cd50ae276e761e97b78f14465343b69277764"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437295 - Ensure cleanup functions registered in a subtest are invoked when unloading the subtest. r=botond\n\nIf we are registering a cleanup function inside a subtest (as we will do\nin the next patch) then we need to make sure it gets cleaned up before\nthe subtest is unloaded. Otherwise the cleanup will be attempted when\nthe top-level test page is unloaded, at which point the subtest is long\ngone, and that results in an error.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 828XddkOUlP", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/apz_test_utils.js", "gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/helper_touch_action_regions.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "81cbeed3386036397f7d001234e89a378a3725c9", "parents": ["e2d541a790ea4419dc366ac9dc5d76a7ece662fc"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437295 - Ensure that waitUntilApzStable also flushes the parent process. r=botond\n\nWith e10s enabled, we need to make sure that not only has the content\nprocess layer tree reached the compositor, but also that the parent\nprocess layer tree with the correct RefLayer has reached the compositor.\nThis is important for some APZ tests which proceed on the assumption\nthat the content process has been composited.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: D0peZsJMHNT", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/apz_test_utils.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "49393cd5db235a279576b857d83232ee2e44c7ed", "parents": ["81cbeed3386036397f7d001234e89a378a3725c9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437295 - Remove unnecessary change from bug 1374166. r=botond\n\nThe change that was made in bug 1374166 was attempting to fix the\nproblem fixed by the previous patch, but didn't actually succeed (it\njust made it less likely to occur). Now that we have the proper fix we\ncan revert that botched attempt to speed up the test a little bit.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3hWZ6bFTdxb", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/test_bug1151663.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5a973861da6a9d3ecb4e7ba10b744958f98c40b6", "parents": ["49393cd5db235a279576b857d83232ee2e44c7ed"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1437295 - Ensure that we have a compositor APZ testdata before running the test. r=botond\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: zV4J3pChIy", "files": ["gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/apz_test_utils.js", "gfx/layers/apz/test/mochitest/helper_bug1151663.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a89953a3788912162dfdbcd3b549693e6743e0a4", "parents": ["5a973861da6a9d3ecb4e7ba10b744958f98c40b6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Johan Lorenzo \u003cjlorenzo@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444391 - google-play-strings: Use release strings on mozilla-release r=bhearsum,mtabara a=release\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: aHR8CwNyqI", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/google-play-strings/kind.yml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f27de9758107421b8a08d86f67f6a950280505b8", "parents": ["0bc390d8397f210bf67d5ef89b8b07c5ba4d1107"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Brindusan Cristian \u003ccbrindusan@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge mozilla-central to inbound. a=merge CLOSED TREE", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "53802a58a0a98ece8176e6afbc6d70a1eb39e0ac", "parents": ["f27de9758107421b8a08d86f67f6a950280505b8", "e0eacfc97568bc270e61839c60ae787fb76c4f07"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Blandy \u003cjimb@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1438121: Add jit-test async-livecache.js. r=fitzgen\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Jbe1GMPGwKj", "files": ["js/src/jit-test/tests/saved-stacks/async-livecache.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "10b30b796dbf89e0cf054ea37cace173702d93c6", "parents": ["53802a58a0a98ece8176e6afbc6d70a1eb39e0ac"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444502: Remove support for installing unpacked extensions. r=aswan\n\nThis retains support for installing unpacked dictionaries, since Hunspell only\nsupports loading dictionaries from ordinary filesystem paths.\n\nUnpacked extensions are no longer supported on production, except during\ndevelopment. WebExtensions have no support for the unpacked flag at all, and\nspecially signed legacy extensions are forbidden from using it, so there's no\npoint in maintaining support for this install code. Or, more importantly, for\nrunning a nearly complete duplicated set of tests in order to exercise it.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1fKVgSelJQ8", "files": ["modules/libpref/init/all.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/internal/XPIInstall.jsm", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/internal/XPIProvider.jsm", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/data/test_bug526598_1.xpi", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/data/test_bug526598_2.xpi", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/data/test_bug541420.xpi", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/head_unpack.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_bug526598.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_bug541420.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_distribution.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_filepointer.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell-shared.ini", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell-unpack.ini", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b8b11082ff88a050a88c1c616b7ed6ffcfc60f76", "parents": ["10b30b796dbf89e0cf054ea37cace173702d93c6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Csoregi Natalia \u003cncsoregi@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge inbound to mozilla-central.  a=merge", "files": ["toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/data/test_bug526598_1.xpi", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/data/test_bug526598_2.xpi", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/data/test_bug541420.xpi", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_bug526598.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_bug541420.js", "toolkit/mozapps/extensions/test/xpcshell/xpcshell-shared.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "8863806b9e28e9a5267c34c2e000f3cc0265f944", "parents": ["a89953a3788912162dfdbcd3b549693e6743e0a4", "b8b11082ff88a050a88c1c616b7ed6ffcfc60f76"], "tags": []}, {"author": "ffxbld", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug, Automated HSTS preload list update from host bld-linux64-spot-302 - a=hsts-update", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.errors", "security/manager/ssl/nsSTSPreloadList.inc"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "26d7052f374999cd06b889e9387bd462531d5c15", "parents": ["8863806b9e28e9a5267c34c2e000f3cc0265f944"], "tags": []}, {"author": "ffxbld", "branch": "default", "desc": "No bug, Automated HPKP preload list update from host bld-linux64-spot-302 - a=hpkp-update", "files": ["security/manager/ssl/StaticHPKPins.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0471c6ccf344ed039d0c514e254a7edbdb8a5905", "parents": ["26d7052f374999cd06b889e9387bd462531d5c15"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Florian Wagner \u003cflorian.wagner@student.hpi.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "servo: Merge #20185 - Make KeyframesPercentage::parse faster (from Beta-Alf:master); r=emilio\n\nMinor refactoring of the parsing of keyframes.\n\n---\n\u003c!-- Thank you for contributing to Servo! Please replace each `[ ]` by `[X]` when the step is complete, and replace `__` with appropriate data: --\u003e\n- [X] `./mach build -d` does not report any errors\n- [X] `./mach test-tidy` does not report any errors\n- [X] These changes fix  #20179 (github issue number if applicable).\n\n\u003c!-- Either: --\u003e\n- [ ] There are tests for these changes OR\n- [X] These changes do not require tests because it is a minor refactor so tests are already in place. The original Issue explicitly says so.\n\n\u003c!-- Also, please make sure that \"Allow edits from maintainers\" checkbox is checked, so that we can help you if you get stuck somewhere along the way.--\u003e\n\n\u003c!-- Pull requests that do not address these steps are welcome, but they will require additional verification as part of the review process. --\u003e\n\nSource-Repo: https://github.com/servo/servo\nSource-Revision: 29e10d4f88a7564f4d6a4496d3d1be5949962f8a", "files": ["servo/components/style/stylesheets/keyframes_rule.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7248a330fafe03c0350c10ab1cf438c0f194793e", "parents": ["8863806b9e28e9a5267c34c2e000f3cc0265f944"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443853 - Remove unnecessary paranthesis around function argument. r=jgraham\n\nSilences one compiler warning.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FSKV9Ia2iXt", "files": ["testing/geckodriver/src/marionette.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b6a8d0f3c88d7d70c4cb8bcc30e802c78d8ac77f", "parents": ["7248a330fafe03c0350c10ab1cf438c0f194793e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443853 - Drop unused std::ascii::AsciiExt trait. r=jgraham\n\nSilences another compiler warning.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6Bcw7Ej9uIC", "files": ["testing/mozbase/rust/mozrunner/src/runner.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "985f63927da9e993ba879ff37d3f1c8b35740319", "parents": ["b6a8d0f3c88d7d70c4cb8bcc30e802c78d8ac77f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443853 - Rename RunnerProcess::is_running() to ::running(). r=jgraham\n\nThe ideom for getters in Rust is to not prefix them with \"is_\".\nSetters should, however, have the \"set_\" prefix.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9kXHBYGK7aL", "files": ["testing/geckodriver/src/marionette.rs", "testing/mozbase/rust/mozrunner/src/runner.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4988c81161f2abe3ecc8640b1d705cd281d92c35", "parents": ["985f63927da9e993ba879ff37d3f1c8b35740319"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443853 - Rename RunnerProcess::stop() to ::kill(). r=jgraham\n\nThis renames RunnerProcess::stop() to ::kill() for symmetry with\nthe standard library's std::process::Child.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 20vSni9bA0X", "files": ["testing/geckodriver/src/marionette.rs", "testing/mozbase/rust/mozrunner/src/runner.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1730b54d8ebf0221c1c3c2f20ed8404c25c8bd9b", "parents": ["4988c81161f2abe3ecc8640b1d705cd281d92c35"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443853 - Avoid std::io::{Result,Error} renaming. r=jgraham\n\nWe can pick up std::io::Result and std::io::Error directly from\nthe std::io namespace without having to rename them.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9Xz92HvcFpO", "files": ["testing/mozbase/rust/mozrunner/src/runner.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "83bb33caf3d352237970d0be2accad0c8378e59d", "parents": ["1730b54d8ebf0221c1c3c2f20ed8404c25c8bd9b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443853 - Rename RunnerProcess::status() to ::try_wait(). r=jgraham\n\nThis renames RunnerProcess::status() to ::try_wait() for symmetry\nwith std::process::Child::try_wait() in the standard library.\n\nThe patch also makes an attempt at cleaning up its usage in geckodriver,\nhowever this can be further improved.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 14ihT7MpM7l", "files": ["testing/geckodriver/src/marionette.rs", "testing/mozbase/rust/mozrunner/src/runner.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2da49990b24780b797b7371ed9d54acc7641d20f", "parents": ["83bb33caf3d352237970d0be2accad0c8378e59d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Tolfsen \u003cato@sny.no\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443853 - Move browser process shutdown monitor to mozrunner. r=jgraham\n\nThis moves the shutdown monitor for the Firefox process from\ngeckodriver to mozrunner, which is a more suitable home for it.\nWe will likely need specialised versions of this in the future with\nproducts such as GeckoView and Fennec.\n\nIn addition to the move it also cleans up the polling loop by\nemploying std::time::SystemTime which lets us match on the elapsed\ntime since its construction.  This seems nicer than having to perform\ndivision operations on integers, which in Rust are inherently unsafe\n(there is no guard against SIGFPE).\n\nThis change should be functionally equivalent to the existing code.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1asnFbixhcY", "files": ["testing/geckodriver/src/marionette.rs", "testing/mozbase/rust/mozrunner/src/runner.rs"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a5d22f442915eaeca18002aa555aa22936f6c855", "parents": ["2da49990b24780b797b7371ed9d54acc7641d20f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "arthur.iakab \u003caiakab@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Merge autoland to mozilla-central. a=merge", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null, null], "node": "6d0d32f6570d875ae9191c07be0355e9083114e8", "parents": ["0471c6ccf344ed039d0c514e254a7edbdb8a5905", "a5d22f442915eaeca18002aa555aa22936f6c855"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Robert Longson \u003clongsonr@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444666 - get rid of nsSVGUtils version of GetStrokeDashData and replace by SVGContentUtils::GetStrokeOptions r=jwatt", "files": ["dom/svg/SVGContentUtils.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxContext.cpp", "gfx/thebes/gfxContext.h", "layout/svg/SVGContextPaint.h", "layout/svg/nsSVGUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "54ed9f585985091fa72251007ffd66b594b665f0", "parents": ["8863806b9e28e9a5267c34c2e000f3cc0265f944"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Taubert \u003cttaubert@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1430150 - Implement WebAuthentication permission prompts r=jcj,johannh\n\nReviewers: jcj, johannh\n\nReviewed By: jcj, johannh\n\nBug #: 1430150\n\nDifferential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D638", "files": ["browser/base/content/browser.css", "browser/base/content/browser.js", "browser/installer/package-manifest.in", "browser/locales/en-US/chrome/browser/browser.properties", "dom/u2f/U2F.cpp", "dom/webauthn/PWebAuthnTransaction.ipdl", "dom/webauthn/U2FHIDTokenManager.cpp", "dom/webauthn/U2FSoftTokenManager.cpp", "dom/webauthn/U2FTokenManager.cpp", "dom/webauthn/U2