cks\nwith their actual usage.\n\nThe changes are:\n\n1. Create the TextureReadLock in the TextureClient constructor so it's available before IPC creation\n    a. This is superficial as EnableReadLock was always called before IPC creation\n2. Send the ReadLockDescriptor in the PTextureConstructor message and close the file handle\n3. Receive the ReadLockDescriptor in TextureHost and close the file handle\n4. Send a boolean flag in layer transactions if the texture is read locked instead of a descriptor\n5. Use a boolean flag in TextureHost to determine if the ReadLock must be unlocked instead of a nullptr\n\nI believe that we can remove the InitReadLocks code from LayerTransaction as that was added to\nprevent file descriptor limits in IPDL messages and is no longer needed with this change. But\nthat is a non-essential change and this patch is already big enough.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: DzHujrOQejH", "files": ["gfx/layers/CompositorTypes.h", "gfx/layers/PersistentBufferProvider.cpp", "gfx/layers/client/CanvasClient.cpp", "gfx/layers/client/ContentClient.cpp", "gfx/layers/client/SingleTiledContentClient.cpp", "gfx/layers/client/TextureClient.cpp", "gfx/layers/client/TextureClient.h", "gfx/layers/client/TiledContentClient.cpp", "gfx/layers/composite/TextureHost.cpp", "gfx/layers/composite/TextureHost.h", "gfx/layers/composite/TiledContentHost.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositableTransactionParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeChild.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeChild.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/CrossProcessCompositorBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/CrossProcessCompositorBridgeParent.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/ImageBridgeChild.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/ImageBridgeChild.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/ImageBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/ImageBridgeParent.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/LayersMessages.ipdlh", "gfx/layers/ipc/PCompositorBridge.ipdl", "gfx/layers/ipc/PImageBridge.ipdl", "gfx/layers/ipc/PVideoBridge.ipdl", "gfx/layers/ipc/ShadowLayers.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/TextureForwarder.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/VideoBridgeChild.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/VideoBridgeChild.h", "gfx/layers/ipc/VideoBridgeParent.cpp", "gfx/layers/ipc/VideoBridgeParent.h", "gfx/layers/wr/WebRenderBridgeChild.cpp", "gfx/tests/gtest/TextureHelper.h", "ipc/glue/CrossProcessSemaphore.h", "ipc/glue/CrossProcessSemaphore_posix.cpp", "ipc/glue/CrossProcessSemaphore_unimplemented.cpp", "ipc/glue/CrossProcessSemaphore_windows.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "395d409b9bf52b975a8b29b81a3e00472c9f0f6e", "parents": ["6a3b458db3be8f2c65bebe84b25ef42d467c9695"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 1 - [css-grid] Change the track sizing algorithm for spanning items so that it accumulates individual item contributions to the plan by max() rather than incrementing the planned size directly.  r=dholbert a=jcristau\n\nAlso, fix a bug when copying back the planned limits after\nupdating it for the first span group.  It should only copy\nback track sizes that were actaully spanned by those items,\nother content-sized tracks' limits should remain at \"infinity\".", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "44425feb2d2022b8dd5ba91a9d86bedbba0e00c9", "parents": ["395d409b9bf52b975a8b29b81a3e00472c9f0f6e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 2 - [css-grid] Factor out the min-sizing parts of the track sizing for spanned items to a templated method (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "934d0c726031ac7938b12414b56bc7c7bd340d01", "parents": ["44425feb2d2022b8dd5ba91a9d86bedbba0e00c9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 3 - [css-grid] Factor out most of the max-sizing parts of the track sizing for spanned items to a templated method (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2405110bef04d0ba709c8e96a2a6d890986a1293", "parents": ["934d0c726031ac7938b12414b56bc7c7bd340d01"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 4 - [css-grid] Factor out the starting base/limit size to a templated method (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a2d9cdb47e6257ac02696f6ce0a9432c6c485c39", "parents": ["2405110bef04d0ba709c8e96a2a6d890986a1293"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 5 - [css-grid] Make CollectGrowable a templated method so that it works with either base/limit sizes (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "7a68f2b6d545736d3ac78a17dca935c227de6709", "parents": ["a2d9cdb47e6257ac02696f6ce0a9432c6c485c39"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 6 - [css-grid] Make the size distribution methods templated with the intent of merging them in a later patch (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau\n\nThis patch also introduces an eInfinitelyGrowable bit to help\nget rid of the 'limits' temporary track sizes in the next patch.", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "fc18102d61a79ab7c3da3f313b14264e0ed949bf", "parents": ["7a68f2b6d545736d3ac78a17dca935c227de6709"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 7 - [css-grid] Remove the 'limits' copy of track sizes since they are no longer needed (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8d563458696dcdaf8f60c1b3cc6e936e58b39fa5", "parents": ["fc18102d61a79ab7c3da3f313b14264e0ed949bf"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 8 - [css-grid] Factor out the fit-content clamping function from DistributeToTrackLimits and pass it as a param instead (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "58331302df7612830f4049907bfc6a738c5fdc17", "parents": ["8d563458696dcdaf8f60c1b3cc6e936e58b39fa5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 9 - [css-grid] Merge DistributeToTrackLimits/Bases (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6dba9c6e951f01da0e34f57da853a739c9dc29df", "parents": ["58331302df7612830f4049907bfc6a738c5fdc17"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 10 - [css-grid] Make MarkExcludedTracks a static method since it doesn't use 'this' (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "c8c86f719155e279cb7e2d102aaaa07dd12278cd", "parents": ["6dba9c6e951f01da0e34f57da853a739c9dc29df"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 11 - [css-grid] Hoist the marking of excluded tracks out from GrowSelectedTracksUnlimited to a separate method (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f542fec596d962d589b76eb3ce3a44ad7f5db448", "parents": ["c8c86f719155e279cb7e2d102aaaa07dd12278cd"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 12 - [css-grid] Merge CopyPlanToBase/Limits into a templated method instead (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ce0dfee9798f6fcdd0fe19f796df932ce5297173", "parents": ["f542fec596d962d589b76eb3ce3a44ad7f5db448"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 13 - [css-grid] Merge Grow[Base|Limits]ForSpanningItems into a templated method instead (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d4d1f62c6211474ead3f8a7a80b40215219456c6", "parents": ["ce0dfee9798f6fcdd0fe19f796df932ce5297173"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 14 - [css-grid] Use iterators instead of an array + start/end index for the item data (idempotent change).  r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5d5e3495dbe795bc265cc8c8ceeff969973fdd27", "parents": ["d4d1f62c6211474ead3f8a7a80b40215219456c6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 15 - [css-grid] Test reference fixes + more tests. r=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/test/mochitest.ini", "layout/generic/test/test_grid_track_sizing_algo_001.html", "layout/generic/test/test_grid_track_sizing_algo_002.html", "layout/reftests/css-grid/grid-col-max-sizing-max-content-001-ref.html", "layout/reftests/css-grid/grid-col-max-sizing-max-content-002-ref.html", "layout/reftests/css-grid/grid-flex-min-sizing-002-ref.html", "layout/reftests/css-grid/grid-max-sizing-flex-004-ref.html", "layout/reftests/css-grid/grid-track-intrinsic-sizing-002-ref.html", "layout/reftests/css-grid/grid-track-intrinsic-sizing-003-ref.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a37d1635609afab310f0e27e8eafcda031aa7e3d", "parents": ["5d5e3495dbe795bc265cc8c8ceeff969973fdd27"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 part 16 - [css-grid] Make SizeContributionForPhase a template.  rs=dholbert a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d67280b77e23f7ae7b18ff2a28a3bc88261cbb78", "parents": ["a37d1635609afab310f0e27e8eafcda031aa7e3d"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Mats Palmgren \u003cmats@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1425599 - [css-grid] Follow-up bustage fix for stupid compiler warnings.  r=mpalmgren a=jcristau", "files": ["layout/generic/nsGridContainerFrame.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b4987640fadead26f71bc7666c106feaacf855f7", "parents": ["d67280b77e23f7ae7b18ff2a28a3bc88261cbb78"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521636688, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "rgurzau@mozilla.com"}, "8890": {"changesets": [{"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444588 - Move LRUCache Initialization to startup rather than lazily. r=baku a=jcristau\n\nBefore, we would initialize LRUCache on the first instance of\ncalling the Timer Precision Reduction functions. We would both\nallocate and initialize it, and call ClearOnShutdown.\n\nClearOnShutdown can only be called on the Main Thread, but it\njust so happened that we always did that, so there was no\nproblem. Now that we are not calling precision reduction for\nsystem callers, we were initializing on a non-main-thread and\nwe need to avoid that.\n\nIn the future, we could reduce memory use IF we are not using\nthe timer precision reduction functions by figuring out how\nto initialize this lazily but still on the main thread. For\nnow, because we are using the timer precision reduction\nfunctions, doing so would not save us any memory.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 6YGeAlCPReZ", "files": ["toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a26ab71d2540d93913c0b41cbaafcc1fbd267eac", "parents": ["b4987640fadead26f71bc7666c106feaacf855f7"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521636997, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8891": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kirk Steuber \u003cksteuber@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1429160 - Create enterprise policy to disable PDF.js. r=dthayer,felipe a=jcristau", "files": ["browser/components/enterprisepolicies/Policies.jsm", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/schemas/policies-schema.json", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/tests/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/tests/browser/browser_policy_disable_pdfjs.js", "browser/extensions/pdfjs/content/PdfJs.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2ac6479eca3f8b75699b131ee6b8754ec9350882", "parents": ["a26ab71d2540d93913c0b41cbaafcc1fbd267eac"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443943 Port the performance APIs only to only clamping/jittering on non-System Principal r=baku a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FKYLI5Yc1kX", "files": ["dom/base/nsGlobalWindowInner.cpp", "dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.cpp", "dom/performance/Performance.cpp", "dom/performance/Performance.h", "dom/performance/PerformanceMainThread.cpp", "dom/performance/PerformanceNavigationTiming.h", "dom/performance/PerformanceStorageWorker.cpp", "dom/performance/PerformanceTiming.cpp", "dom/performance/PerformanceTiming.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "80d6f981383abdbdce2c46a9fa22b02eb231cd02", "parents": ["2ac6479eca3f8b75699b131ee6b8754ec9350882"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443943 Do not clamp/jitter in the JS Engine if it's system context r=jorendorff,luke a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LqL7xaYoHCT", "files": ["dom/base/nsGlobalWindowOuter.cpp", "dom/workers/WorkerPrivate.cpp", "js/src/jsapi.h", "js/src/jsdate.cpp", "js/xpconnect/src/Sandbox.cpp", "js/xpconnect/src/nsXPConnect.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ec9f524f70c507c7ba1dec1a3ac6c8700f7ac88c", "parents": ["80d6f981383abdbdce2c46a9fa22b02eb231cd02"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443943 Do not clamp/jitter event timestamps if it's a system principal r=baku a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KvVJpvu4elN", "files": ["dom/events/Event.cpp", "dom/events/Event.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bd233781f767e4809df886b76af51c777104f441", "parents": ["ec9f524f70c507c7ba1dec1a3ac6c8700f7ac88c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443943 Allow internal callers of performance.now() to opt-out of clamping/jittering r=bholley a=jcristau\n\nPresShell only uses performane.now to track refresh times, and notify internal\nobservers. We can provide more accurate times by not clamping and jittering\nthese numbers.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FkDGJhrLeAy", "files": ["dom/performance/Performance.cpp", "dom/performance/Performance.h", "layout/base/PresShell.cpp", "layout/base/PresShell.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e3104f4386e8e9e1f0461ea1196dc38f5aa46534", "parents": ["bd233781f767e4809df886b76af51c777104f441"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1440195 Add a per-context mix-in value for our Timer Precision Reduction Functions r=baku a=jcristau\n\nWe need to include a seed for each context (origin, iframe, worker, etc) we reduce\nthe time precision of. This prevents a replay attack of the random midpoint sequence.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: EFoHev1SrTM", "files": ["toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/RelativeTimeline.cpp", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/RelativeTimeline.h", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/moz.build", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.cpp", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.h", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/tests/test_reduceprecision.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e2434dc015192883bdb5cd01012d1b4d38ca5747", "parents": ["e3104f4386e8e9e1f0461ea1196dc38f5aa46534"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1440195 For timestamps that are absolute, specify a null context pointer r=baku a=jcristau\n\nNote that by not using the same context pointer for all timestamps within a single\n'communication group' (that is, all things that can communication to each other\nin JavaScript), it's possible to observe time going backwards.\n\nImagine comparing\n  performance.timeOrigin + performance.now() \u003c new File([], \"\").lastModified\n\nIn theory this should always be true. However, if performance.now() was jittered\nup (using one context pointer, because it is a relative timestamp) and File was\njittered down (using a null context pointer, because it is an absolute timestamp)\nthen this may evaluate to False.\n\nI think this is okay.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BfgbmGS8XdD", "files": ["dom/file/BaseBlobImpl.cpp", "dom/file/MultipartBlobImpl.cpp", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f5fca57484d031e2337eb959d857107207c8f21a", "parents": ["e2434dc015192883bdb5cd01012d1b4d38ca5747"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1440195 Add a random context seed for AudioContext and MediaStream r=baku a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: sHpVCgd8Fs", "files": ["dom/media/DOMMediaStream.cpp", "dom/media/DOMMediaStream.h", "dom/media/webaudio/AudioContext.cpp", "dom/media/webaudio/AudioContext.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "86ba2db234ae739265e73a863a0ed3c4360bcc35", "parents": ["f5fca57484d031e2337eb959d857107207c8f21a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1440195 Add a random context seed to the Performance APIs r=baku a=jcristau\n\nWe attach it to WorkerPrivate and DOMNavigationTiming so it will be re-used\nwhen it should.\n\nWorkerPrivate is used in the Performance APIs, Performance Storage Worker,\nand Event.\n\nDOMNavigationTiming is used only in the Performance APIs, but the crucial\npart is that when the individual DOMNavigationTiming object is re-used,\nso will the context seed. This in particular came up with the\nnav2_test_document_open.html Web Platform Test which illustrated the fact\nthat even if you .open() a new document, the performance navigation data\nis not supposed to change.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GIv6biEo2jY", "files": ["dom/base/nsDOMNavigationTiming.h", "dom/events/Event.cpp", "dom/performance/Performance.cpp", "dom/performance/Performance.h", "dom/performance/PerformanceMainThread.cpp", "dom/performance/PerformanceMainThread.h", "dom/performance/PerformanceNavigationTiming.h", "dom/performance/PerformanceStorageWorker.cpp", "dom/performance/PerformanceTiming.cpp", "dom/performance/PerformanceTiming.h", "dom/performance/PerformanceWorker.cpp", "dom/performance/PerformanceWorker.h", "dom/workers/WorkerPrivate.cpp", "dom/workers/WorkerPrivate.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "cf00a5369f69f6c5b478e4a5018cabe09a8b9a81", "parents": ["86ba2db234ae739265e73a863a0ed3c4360bcc35"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1440195 Address CSS Animations r=birtles a=jcristau\n\nFor now, we are going to make _all_ CSS Animations related timer fuzzing\nonly applicable in Resist Fingerprinting Mode (addressing the last couple\nthat had not already been configured that way.)\n\nWe hardcode their content mix-ins as zero, but leave comments indicating\nhow they should behave.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: KhmV7wO8Pt5", "files": ["dom/animation/AnimationUtils.h", "layout/style/nsAnimationManager.cpp", "layout/style/nsTransitionManager.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "0b094ed5c2f8d8de1f445f371cb07da3c1ce449b", "parents": ["cf00a5369f69f6c5b478e4a5018cabe09a8b9a81"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1440195 Actually integrate the context mix-in into the hash function calculation r=baku a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 4k7w683UJOY", "files": ["toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.cpp", "toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/tests/test_reduceprecision.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "683adcd07af8f28f22efaf69a03647b7532f9507", "parents": ["0b094ed5c2f8d8de1f445f371cb07da3c1ce449b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tom Ritter \u003ctom@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1440195 Do not check for NSS Initialization before performing jitter r=keeler a=jcristau\n\nPreviously we needed this check because we were jittering before NSS was initialized\nand this was causing tests to fail (primarily xpcshell and Marionette) because\nNSS was being initialied before there was a profile directory.\n\nIn Bug 1443943 we only jitter non-System Principal calls and that reduces the early\njitter causes. Ultimately we got to a place where everything was looking okay whether\nor not NSS was initialized by the time we got here, so we can simply this code and\nsimply always perform jittering (if it's enabled and we're not in System Principal\ncode.)\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Dgfi8Z1hHfB", "files": ["toolkit/components/resistfingerprinting/nsRFPService.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "15e6ad92c29debadafe8f3d20e8157aedc0f7d82", "parents": ["683adcd07af8f28f22efaf69a03647b7532f9507"], "tags": []}, {"author": "D\u00e3o Gottwald \u003cdao@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443937 - Make the autoscroll popup explicitly consume outside clicks. r=enn a=jcristau", "files": ["toolkit/content/widgets/browser.xml"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "86165d0549cead8e5a3564c6a2cd53a75ea8ca66", "parents": ["15e6ad92c29debadafe8f3d20e8157aedc0f7d82"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521637604, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "rgurzau@mozilla.com"}, "8892": {"changesets": [{"author": "David Parks \u003cdparks@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1445471 - Recognize invalid HANDLEs in plugin brokering. r=jimm a=jcristau\n\nWhen InternetOpenA, or some other brokered function that returns handles, fails, we should not return a valid HANDLE id.  We return an id of 0 instead.", "files": ["dom/plugins/ipc/FunctionBroker.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "382437b9db024f51e49655de0a61885b35352813", "parents": ["86165d0549cead8e5a3564c6a2cd53a75ea8ca66"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Myk Melez \u003cmyk@mykzilla.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1445991 - ensure prefs inited before autoconfig reload button updated; r=Gijs a=jcristau\n\nReorder the construction of Preference objects so network.proxy.autoconfig_url gets constructed before network.proxy.type, which will ensure that networkProxyAutoconfigURL is set to the value of network.proxy.autoconfig_url before network.proxy.type construction triggers the call to updateReloadButton.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: BQL0RlvnCOo", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/connection.js", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser.ini", "browser/components/preferences/in-content/tests/browser_connection_bug1445991.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4f2e5b33fec12d0763e686a338aec7f779d7bf54", "parents": ["382437b9db024f51e49655de0a61885b35352813"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kirk Steuber \u003cksteuber@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1447051 - about:preferences should not offer to Preview PDFs when the DisableBuiltinPDFViewer policy is active r=bdahl,Felipe a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: B2R6SUbAyXP", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/main.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "013a1953f0fc8a5e4f5cd76afeb63903c0f0a964", "parents": ["4f2e5b33fec12d0763e686a338aec7f779d7bf54"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1447105 - Remove boolean enums so GPOs work. r=Felipe a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Cso5ysv1DYE", "files": ["browser/components/enterprisepolicies/schemas/policies-schema.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1244252489a7491013bb0aaf81b5b07a24514159", "parents": ["013a1953f0fc8a5e4f5cd76afeb63903c0f0a964"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521639343, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null], "user": "ncsoregi@mozilla.com"}, "8893": {"changesets": [{"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444506 - part 1 - update to Skia m66. r=jrmuizel, a=jcristau", "files": ["gfx/skia/skia/include/android/SkAndroidFrameworkUtils.h", "gfx/skia/skia/include/android/SkAnimatedImage.h", "gfx/skia/skia/include/android/SkBitmapRegionDecoder.h", "gfx/skia/skia/include/atlastext/SkAtlasTextContext.h", "gfx/skia/skia/include/atlastext/SkAtlasTextFont.h", "gfx/skia/skia/include/atlastext/SkAtlasTextRenderer.h", "gfx/skia/skia/include/atlastext/SkAtlasTextTarg