ervice worker interception. r=asuth, a=jcristau", "files": ["dom/serviceworkers/ServiceWorkerEvents.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9c0b076211c6f281d0f148c4e4441bc22ee3a52b", "parents": ["be657736c061665f56593834e2e09814ae9126b6"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ben Kelly \u003cben@wanderview.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443850 - Part 2: Add a WPT test verifying synthetic responses work when a request fragment is present. r=asuth, a=jcristau", "files": ["testing/web-platform/meta/MANIFEST.json", "testing/web-platform/tests/service-workers/service-worker/fetch-event.https.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "267e76b56a4b7ba0de0d6b0d813fd4cde3d4f27e", "parents": ["9c0b076211c6f281d0f148c4e4441bc22ee3a52b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1443771 - Add ESR name to the about dialog. It is not translated. r=Felipe,jaws, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: FYjA7IrTGYt", "files": ["browser/base/content/aboutDialog.css", "browser/base/content/aboutDialog.js", "browser/base/content/aboutDialog.xul"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9ba5a964b20dd15e4de2a9c4dd29ee285f969208", "parents": ["267e76b56a4b7ba0de0d6b0d813fd4cde3d4f27e"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Patrick Brosset \u003cpbrosset@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444327 - Bring back ability to see and copy font URLs. r=jdescottes, a=jcristau, l10n=flod\n\nIn the fonts panel UI prior to Firefox 60, remote font URLs used to be\ndisplayed in full in a text input field. It made it easy to copy them.\nWith the redesign that happened in 60 (bug 1437548 and 1442001), getting\nthe URL became harder. The URL isn't visible anymore easily. There's a link\nthat can be clicked to load the URL in the browser, or it can also be copied\nfrom the @font-face CSS rule code section. But that's harder.\n\nThis change adds the beginning of the URL back (with an ellipsis) and a\nsimple button that copies the link.\n\nNote that the new test failed intermittently on non e10s (took too long).\nThis was because of a react middleware which was logging all actions, which,\nin non-e10s, ended up logging StyleRuleActors, which got serialized and caused\nway too much logs to be printed, slowing the test down. So the test was\ndisabled on non-e10s.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2oSMoWKYhTk", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/fonts/components/Font.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/test/browser.ini", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/test/browser_fontinspector.js", "devtools/client/inspector/fonts/test/browser_fontinspector_copy-URL.js", "devtools/client/jar.mn", "devtools/client/locales/en-US/font-inspector.properties", "devtools/client/themes/fonts.css", "devtools/client/themes/images/copy.svg"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f304fa7bc72e5cb702245962bb2d60eac7dc9cd3", "parents": ["9ba5a964b20dd15e4de2a9c4dd29ee285f969208"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521655062, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "8896": {"changesets": [{"author": "Sebastian Hengst \u003carchaeopteryx@coole-files.de\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444327 - Bring back ability to see and copy font URLs: Add whitespace to make eslint happy. r=eslint a=eslint-fix", "files": ["devtools/client/inspector/fonts/test/browser_fontinspector_copy-URL.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "8be55a86ae3b06ce9edce3df2ee8caafd5188e4b", "parents": ["f304fa7bc72e5cb702245962bb2d60eac7dc9cd3"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521657453, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "archaeopteryx@coole-files.de"}, "8897": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nit -\u003e 35c6d2a60988", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "498f0dcae2b08f4139a642ccd4e2b2d49554c913", "parents": ["8be55a86ae3b06ce9edce3df2ee8caafd5188e4b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521660014, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8898": {"changesets": [{"author": "L10n Bumper Bot \u003crelease+l10nbumper@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "no bug - Bumping Firefox l10n changesets DONTBUILD r=release a=l10n-bump\n\nit -\u003e 0d7455958144", "files": ["browser/locales/l10n-changesets.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "dcc0f4782b121690683cecf01663914e6874e2eb", "parents": ["498f0dcae2b08f4139a642ccd4e2b2d49554c913"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521663619, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ffxbld"}, "8899": {"changesets": [{"author": "Kris Maglione \u003cmaglione.k@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1409888 - Whitelist expected promise rejection. a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: JR3A5rYLmwD", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_idle.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d7bf437cc217eb9e3591950ac54c2653f8c2f07c", "parents": ["dcc0f4782b121690683cecf01663914e6874e2eb"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Hiroyuki Ikezoe \u003chikezoe@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444177 - Tweak expected restyle count for the test case where finite animation is unthrottled in out-of-view element. r=birtles, a=test-only\n\nIt might be possible that the animation does not start being restyled in the\ninitial frame.  Eventually we should drop tweakExpectedRestyleCount in bug\n1425778 and replace it with a function that waits for animation.ready and waits\nto start being restyled something like this;\n\n  async function waitForAnimationReadyToBeRestyled(aAnimation) {\n    await aAnimation.ready;\n\n    if (animationStartsRightNow(aAnimation)) {\n      await waitForFrame();\n    }\n  }\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: ByN25hMAK76", "files": ["dom/animation/test/mozilla/file_restyles.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "db9a442c2d731cf3362f4b79d7214caf0c230a32", "parents": ["d7bf437cc217eb9e3591950ac54c2653f8c2f07c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eliza Balazs \u003cebalazs@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1262679 - Edited the test case. r=jmaher, a=test-only", "files": ["toolkit/content/tests/widgets/test_videocontrols_standalone.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6776c57cdbb9432346a9ebc125adfd7ba09fb1b3", "parents": ["db9a442c2d731cf3362f4b79d7214caf0c230a32"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Gijs Kruitbosch \u003cgijskruitbosch@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1423938 - Try to fix browser_bug537474 detecting about:blank loads in the selected tab. r=johannh, a=test-only\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: cLfN049EJt", "files": ["browser/base/content/test/general/browser_bug537474.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "82c067be1c575ede5ebbe080a2a4505aa52b074f", "parents": ["6776c57cdbb9432346a9ebc125adfd7ba09fb1b3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Chris AtLee \u003ccatlee@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1446241 - Set run-on-projects for upload-generated-sources and upload-symbols. r=aki, a=RyanVM\n\nIf tasks still exist before the optimization phase, then any tasks these depend\non will also be scheduled. In particular for devedition on m-r, that means that\nalthough the builds were being excluded from the target tasks due to the\nbuild's run-on-projects settings, the upload-symbols and\nupload-generated-sources tasks did exist in the target tasks, and so the builds\ngot re-added to the target tasks during graph optimization.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1AWJuafULEE", "files": ["taskcluster/ci/upload-generated-sources/kind.yml", "taskcluster/ci/upload-symbols/kind.yml", "taskcluster/taskgraph/transforms/task.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f38f39a9cd54cf4664a14e0ed23f5d3dd799fd18", "parents": ["82c067be1c575ede5ebbe080a2a4505aa52b074f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Lee Salzman \u003clsalzman@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1438917 - Limit allocations in SkTDynamicHash. r=jrmuizel, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1d3Tngi6Uek", "files": ["gfx/skia/skia/src/core/SkTDynamicHash.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "25c727364e92b35f1a6e7b4f1e23527fb5305474", "parents": ["f38f39a9cd54cf4664a14e0ed23f5d3dd799fd18"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Emilio Cobos \u00c1lvarez \u003cemilio@crisal.io\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1446981 - Wallpaper broken PresShell invariants on Fx60. r=bz, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Lxowvwpxs20", "files": ["layout/base/PresShell.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "58c9fa4cf6520ddcc72351d2ee17b2185449d98e", "parents": ["25c727364e92b35f1a6e7b4f1e23527fb5305474"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Kartikaya Gupta \u003ckgupta@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1447157 - Avoid crashing if an unregistered layer tree gets adopted. r=botond, a=RyanVM\n\nIt looks like we can get layer tree adopted messages when the compositor\ndoesn't have an entry for that layer tree in sIndirectLayerTrees. So we\nneed to null-check all the things we pull out of that structure - all\nthe properties are already null-checked except for the mParent. This\npatch adds a null check around that as well.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 2fb4SdvgSrG", "files": ["gfx/layers/ipc/CompositorBridgeParent.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "bcb37538cf4b4fe1434e486f9b0f063487d52b9b", "parents": ["58c9fa4cf6520ddcc72351d2ee17b2185449d98e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521666140, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "8900": {"changesets": [{"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Backed out changeset d7bf437cc217 (bug 1409888) because it depends on a feature which doesn't exist on 60.", "files": ["toolkit/components/extensions/test/xpcshell/test_ext_idle.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e965291bd708e0b007f8f7adc84349352a63aaac", "parents": ["bcb37538cf4b4fe1434e486f9b0f063487d52b9b"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521667319, "git_changesets": [null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "8901": {"changesets": [{"author": "tbirdbld", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD600b1_2018032119_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Automated checkin: version bump for thunderbird 60.0b1 release. DONTBUILD CLOSED TREE a=release", "files": [], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "f7f12ab57eda5260f42818c1725cbe83d69949c9", "parents": ["f87ba53e04ff338f8c1cec80ec419f112b27cb73"], "tags": ["THUNDERBIRD_60_0b1_BUILD5"]}, {"author": "tbirdbld", "branch": "THUNDERBIRD600b1_2018032119_RELBRANCH", "desc": "Added THUNDERBIRD_60_0b1_RELEASE THUNDERBIRD_60_0b1_BUILD5 tag(s) for changeset f7f12ab57eda. DONTBUILD CLOSED TREE a=release", "files": [".hgtags"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ee6563b5ae66ac5a6dbc721d2dfad5c21fe49512", "parents": ["f7f12ab57eda5260f42818c1725cbe83d69949c9"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521674731, "git_changesets": [null, null], "user": "tbirdbld"}, "8902": {"changesets": [{"author": "Andrew Halberstadt \u003cahalberstadt@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444152 - [test] Fix regression running marionette tests with |mach test|. r=whimboo, a=test-only\n\nThere were two issues:\n1) The mach command name in resolve.py was wrong.\n2) The marionette harness uses deepcopy on the passed in kwargs and sometimes\nthe 'log' argument that testing/mach_commands.py was passing in can be a class\ninstance (which can't be deepcopied).\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 5gPxuiHs3dY", "files": ["testing/marionette/mach_commands.py", "testing/mozbase/moztest/moztest/resolve.py"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4991a778dc7e56faa7ae2fe900069594f0fc0fc4", "parents": ["e965291bd708e0b007f8f7adc84349352a63aaac"], "tags": []}, {"author": "vinoth \u003ccegvinoth@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1414541 - Intermittent failure fixed for toplevel data: URI. r=ckerschb, a=test-only", "files": ["dom/security/test/general/file_block_toplevel_data_navigation.html", "dom/security/test/general/file_block_toplevel_data_navigation3.html", "dom/security/test/general/test_block_toplevel_data_navigation.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "5e65b1aaa5080d71b41d16d9cfa58853c7f08d8a", "parents": ["4991a778dc7e56faa7ae2fe900069594f0fc0fc4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Daniel Holbert \u003cdholbert@cs.stanford.edu\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1335266: In test_fragments.html, don't set iframe src attribute until *after* we've set up its load handler. r=longsonr, a=test-only\n\nThis will hopefully fix some intermittent timeouts that we're hitting in this\ntest. (The theory is that without this patch, maybe we're firing the iframe's\nload event before we've set up the load handler.)\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 183ogex73SX", "files": ["dom/svg/test/test_fragments.html"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "e655623f6ea9f9757c8ff2c18e9849f17cd4cc21", "parents": ["5e65b1aaa5080d71b41d16d9cfa58853c7f08d8a"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Ryan VanderMeulen \u003cryanvm@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1317615 - Skip dom/asmjscache/test/test_slow.html on debug builds for timeouts. a=test-only", "files": ["dom/asmjscache/test/mochitest.ini"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4eb2f83ac54b6d3c976340749ccdd00a34fdc0f8", "parents": ["e655623f6ea9f9757c8ff2c18e9849f17cd4cc21"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Punam \u003cpdahiya@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444521 - Preferences UI save to cloud downloads event listener. r=jaws, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: LbKr1rpXn4q", "files": ["browser/components/preferences/in-content/main.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6d94629619517eda556f0368049a71142d6ff0c2", "parents": ["4eb2f83ac54b6d3c976340749ccdd00a34fdc0f8"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1445935 - HTMLEditRules::SplitMailCites() remove left node of split node if it becomes empty. r=m_kato, a=jcristau\n\nBefore bug 1413181, HTMLEditRules::SplitMailCites() receives left node of\nsplit node with |leftCite| from SplitNodeDeep().  However, the out argument\nwas removed by the bug and now, it can be retrieved with\nSplitNodeResult::GetPreviousNode().  Its result is used for creating \u003cbr\u003e\nelement etc, but not set to |leftCite| but HTMLEditRules::SplitMailCites()\nstill checks if |leftCite| is empty to remove it from the DOM tree.\n\nSo, now, both |leftCite| and |rightCite| are not necessary and\nHTMLEditRules::SplitMailCites() should use |previousNodeOfSplitPoint|\ninstead of |leftCite|.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 408MJt6X1IV", "files": ["editor/libeditor/HTMLEditRules.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "b3e6be69e432949d8707bb9f94c40ee7c2aaff2b", "parents": ["6d94629619517eda556f0368049a71142d6ff0c2"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Masayuki Nakano \u003cmasayuki@d-toybox.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1445929 - Make Editor(Raw)DOMPoint::IsEndOfContainer() check if mParent is container node before checking mChild. r=m_kato, a=jcristau\n\nEditor(Raw)DOMPoint::IsEndOfContainer() checks mIsChildInitialized before\nreferring mChild.  However, it may be true even if mParent is not a container\nnode like a text node.  Therefore, if mParent is a text node and\nmIsChildInitialized is true, it always returns true (i.e., even if mOffset\nisn't same as length of mParent).\n\nThis patch makes it check mParent-\u003eIsContainerNode() before checking\nmIsChildInitialized because after checking mIsChildInitialized, it validates\nthe relation of the members.  So, this keeps the validation simple.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: K2XrAZoNv2I", "files": ["editor/libeditor/EditorDOMPoint.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "ee4ed3b4b94532184cc60db11dbcb52034b560d9", "parents": ["b3e6be69e432949d8707bb9f94c40ee7c2aaff2b"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444541 - Don't stop recorder on pagehide during frameswap. r=smaug, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: AZec0yXM1FI", "files": ["dom/media/MediaRecorder.cpp", "dom/media/moz.build"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2fee5cc3ec3a477802f2a8dddb46b98c9cfef00e", "parents": ["ee4ed3b4b94532184cc60db11dbcb52034b560d9"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Andreas Pehrson \u003cpehrsons@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1435036 - Improve window checks. r=jib, a=RyanVM", "files": ["dom/media/MediaManager.cpp", "dom/media/MediaManager.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "99a22b7c1e8e98d9beb91ebc772526695b0f8ae4", "parents": ["2fee5cc3ec3a477802f2a8dddb46b98c9cfef00e"], "tags": []}], "date": 1521729807, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null], "user": "ryanvm@gmail.com"}, "8903": {"changesets": [{"author": "Jonathan Watt \u003cjwatt@jwatt.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397795 - Fix stack overflow crash due to box-shadow. r=mstange, a=jcristau\n\nGetBoxShadowRectForFrame is called while we're calculating the visual\noverflow bounds for a frame.  So it is not valid for it to use the frame's\n\"current\" visual overflow rect (which may be uninitialized or stale).\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: J52dxIMrMg5", "files": ["layout/base/nsLayoutUtils.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4a040f2fca3068bfa710338ca87eedfae8231db5", "parents": ["99a22b7c1e8e98d9beb91ebc772526695b0f8ae4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Watt \u003cjwatt@jwatt.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397795 part 2 - Crashtest for box-shadow. r=mstange, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 8zEK1R77znx", "files": ["dom/base/crashtests/1397795.html", "dom/base/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d37345171e91d91e70f59b5f4db9c27040f81ef3", "parents": ["4a040f2fca3068bfa710338ca87eedfae8231db5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jonathan Watt \u003cjwatt@jwatt.org\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1397795 part 3 - Don't rely on opaque widgets not having overflow. r=mstange, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: GJNDwQUjfEr", "files": ["devtools/server/actors/highlighters.css", "devtools/server/actors/highlighters/utils/markup.js", "dom/base/crashtests/1026714.html", "dom/base/crashtests/crashtests.list"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "a16f636c81ebb4c995b6d64966557ccde9a4559f", "parents": ["d37345171e91d91e70f59b5f4db9c27040f81ef3"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Barry Chen \u003cchenba@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1447043 - Calculate top and left selection margin using left and top. r=_6a68, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 88TM8xgATPC", "files": ["browser/extensions/screenshots/webextension/selector/ui.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "760683bdddb4a8d4e19444824b2153f5fc53923c", "parents": ["a16f636c81ebb4c995b6d64966557ccde9a4559f"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jared Hirsch \u003cohai@6a68.net\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1447043 - Export Screenshots 30.1.0 to Firefox. r=ianbicking, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9XBAO678lT7", "files": ["browser/extensions/screenshots/install.rdf", "browser/extensions/screenshots/webextension/manifest.json"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "67b517c61b1f86e098a72ec95083c3315086cd9c", "parents": ["760683bdddb4a8d4e19444824b2153f5fc53923c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1447382 - Re-bundle release v19.2 + backports. r=jlast, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 3EPD96pWU42", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/new/debugger.js", "devtools/client/debugger/new/parser-worker.js", "devtools/client/debugger/new/pretty-print-worker.js", "devtools/client/debugger/new/search-worker.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "9452d69547d28c2fbbae8b2dc6dcf581b5381480", "parents": ["67b517c61b1f86e098a72ec95083c3315086cd9c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Julian Descottes \u003cjdescottes@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1447382 - Update Debugger Frontend v19.3. r=jlast, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Bdy4neTgJUp", "files": ["devtools/client/debugger/new/README.mozilla", "devtools/client/debugger/new/debugger.css", "devtools/client/debugger/new/debugger.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "1f86e8c381c66a232d926c62eb2f6272df21f660", "parents": ["9452d69547d28c2fbbae8b2dc6dcf581b5381480"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1433870 - Policy: Tracking protection. r=felipe, r=bytesized, a=jcristau", "files": ["browser/components/enterprisepolicies/Policies.jsm", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/schemas/policies-schema.json", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/tests/browser/browser.ini", "browser/components/enterprisepolicies/tests/browser/browser_policy_enable_tracking_protection.js"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "117ae537ef0d0a989b9505369a28c6a58bdfeae8", "parents": ["1f86e8c381c66a232d926c62eb2f6272df21f660"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Michael Kaply \u003cmozilla@kaply.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1447353 - If tracking protection explicitly disabled, lock it. r=Felipe, a=jcristau\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: Fe2oUOuCJxN", "files": ["browser/components/enterprisepolicies/Policies.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "998a57bd05ada832da0cd78e2db628699afee80e", "parents": ["117ae537ef0d0a989b9505369a28c6a58bdfeae8"], "tags": ["DEVEDITION_60_0b6_BUILD1", "DEVEDITION_60_0b6_RELEASE", "FIREFOX_60_0b6_BUILD1", "FIREFOX_60_0b6_RELEASE"]}], "date": 1521732034, "git_changesets": [null, null, null, null, null, null, null, null,