rEventHandler.cpp", "dom/events/test/pointerevents/test_bug1303704.html", "widget/WidgetEventImpl.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "3954e94774f97771c90bd3b31adc946a9b5222a4", "parents": ["3784b22ec536b08ce95201d73ae8806340c18b8c"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Tim Nguyen \u003cntim.bugs@gmail.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1448867 - Fix .subviewbutton hover/active text color on Linux. r=dao, a=RyanVM\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9PSECYAg9v1", "files": ["browser/themes/shared/customizableui/panelUI.inc.css"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "32c8f13203b34e82f8dd515489080cdbab595ae5", "parents": ["3954e94774f97771c90bd3b31adc946a9b5222a4"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Eugen Sawin \u003cesawin@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1440592 - [4.3] Allow load delegation when opening windows before requesting a new session. r=snorp, a=RyanVM", "files": ["mobile/android/modules/geckoview/GeckoViewNavigation.jsm"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "d244d295cd2b3d8d8255716e37fd3107eaf6df66", "parents": ["32c8f13203b34e82f8dd515489080cdbab595ae5"], "tags": []}, {"author": "David Keeler \u003cdkeeler@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1424311 - Don't persist the certificate exception dialog's size so it doesn't grow unboundedly. r=jcj, a=RyanVM\n\nwindow.sizeToContent() apparently interacts poorly with windows that have a\npersisted size (see bug 90276, which is a 5-digit bug that hasn't been touched\nin over a decade). As a workaround, don't persist the certificate exception\ndialog's size. This means we have to call window.sizeToContent() more often and\nunfortunately results in the window growing and shrinking again on Windows, but\nat least it will always be the \"right size\" for its content.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 9UT3X8IEqZg", "files": ["security/manager/pki/resources/content/exceptionDialog.js", "security/manager/pki/resources/content/exceptionDialog.xul"], "git_node": null, 