hat\nLiveSavedFrameCache::find never runs off the bottom of the cache. But we should\ncheck for an empty cache even in release builds, so that violations of this\ninvariant don't cause unconstrained memory accesses.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: 1b9vx9nvVeY", "files": ["js/src/vm/SavedStacks.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "6d530e6cb06d0249ef87b91ad76a471f3a31d716", "parents": ["23754ad53136c686390597f2ed0228db3013ea21"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Blandy \u003cjimb@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444604 - Part 2: Simplify condition in FrameIter::operator++. r=jorendorff, a=RyanVM\n\nInterpreterFrame::isDebuggerEvalFrame implies ..::evalInFramePrev, so there's no\nneed to check both.\n\nMozReview-Commit-ID: sIuSKhDVSl", "files": ["js/src/vm/Stack.cpp"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "2d48365acd9fb569b6d180e06e26bad9a5b78601", "parents": ["6d530e6cb06d0249ef87b91ad76a471f3a31d716"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Blandy \u003cjimb@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444604 - Part 3: Let SavedStacks::insertFrames construct its own FrameIter. r=jorendorff, a=RyanVM", "files": ["js/src/vm/SavedStacks.cpp", "js/src/vm/SavedStacks.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4518879e214025b16d6e57734c620f136119d246", "parents": ["2d48365acd9fb569b6d180e06e26bad9a5b78601"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Blandy \u003cjimb@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444604 - Part 4: Construct FramePtrs from AbstractFramePtrs. r=jorendorff, a=RyanVM", "files": ["js/src/vm/Stack-inl.h", "js/src/vm/Stack.h"], "git_node": null, "git_parents": [null], "node": "4e8e98727140ceb78123bedbd5044b5ed0e20bd7", "parents": ["4518879e214025b16d6e57734c620f136119d246"], "tags": []}, {"author": "Jim Blandy \u003cjimb@mozilla.com\u003e", "branch": "default", "desc": "Bug 1444604 - Part 5: Downcast FramePtrs to InterpreterFrames. r=jorendorff, a=RyanVM", "files": ["js/src/vm/Stack.h"], "git_node":